  "text": "Another source for the variance of the gradient is the scaling term [Q θ (s, a) − T Q θ − (s, a)] (a similar analysis for the deep generative model is provided in [CITATION_1] ). The following proposition demonstrates for the case without function approximation that, starting from the same initial Q-function, the update for T soft will always be less than the update for T . This result easily generalizes to the Q-learning case if we assume that both updates use the same training data.",
